  "texts": [
    "The former concept was raised by Wei et al.",
    "and it has been proven that it can improve the performance of LLM in multiple kinds of tasks including arithmetic, commonsense, and symbolic reasoning tasks by applying LLM with this kind of principle [14], [15].",
    "On the other hand, the latter focuses on feeding the responses generated from LLM back to LLM with evaluations of human beings to improve the performance of LLM in dealing with a particular kind of task [16], [17].",
    "Both these two concepts influenced the design and implementation of a series of language model-controlling frameworks such as LangChain and Guidance from Microsoft.",
    "These concepts and tools are generic purposes while our multi-phase facilitation agent focuses on facilitation-specific purposes."
  ],
